Before any task, follow these rules:

1. Analyze Existing Code
Understand the current code before adding or changing anything.

2. Improve First
Refactor or enhance existing code; avoid rewriting or duplicating.

3. Modular & Planned
Break code into clear functions/classes/modules; plan steps if needed.

4. Avoid Duplicates
Do not repeat logic; reuse or extract shared components.

5. Review & Be Consistent
Follow project style, naming, correct placement, and check clarity and maintainability.

6. Keep It Simple  
Avoid overengineering. Choose the simplest solution that fits the requirement.

